Lewis Cirne: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 3:19 AM ET
Internet Software and Services

Company Overview of New Relic, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Lewis   Cirne  CEO, Founder & Director, New Relic, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships47$658,776As of Fiscal Year 2017
Background

		Mr. Lewis Cirne, also known as Lew, founded New Relic, Inc. in 2008 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since February 2008. Mr. Cirne serves as a Strategic Limited Partner at The Four Rivers Group. He served as Entrepreneur in Residence of Benchmark Capital since February 15, 2008. He served as Advisor of Pano Logic, Inc. He founded Wily Technology Inc. in 1998 and served as its Chief Technology Officer where he was responsible for sharing with customers and partners ... Wily Technology's vision of bringing enterprise class performance management to the Java platform. Mr. Cirne is a widely cited expert in enterprise application performance and availability. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Wily Technology until October 2001. He takes a leading role in the future technological development of Wily Technology and its products, with the goal of extending the services offered by Wily to customers deploying high-performance e-business solutions. Prior to founding Wily, Mr. Cirne held senior technical positions at Apple Inc. and Hummingbird Ltd. He is a seasoned entrepreneur, technologist and enterprise software pioneer. He has been focused on application performance management for more than 10 years. He has been a Director of New Relic, Inc. since February 2008. He served as Director of Wily Technology, Inc. He holds an A.B. in Computer Science from Dartmouth College.Read Full Background




